American Oilfield Divers relocates . American Oilfield Divers Inc said Tuesday its corporate headquarters has relocated to Houston from Lafayette , La . American Oilfield Divers , founded in 1981 by chairman George Yax , provides subsea services , including diving , to the offshore oil and gas industry . " The move of our corporate headquarters . . . allows us to offer a broader base of support for our growing Gulf Services operations , " chief executive Rod Stanley said . " We will continue our Gulf Services operations at the Port of Iberia , La . , and maintain a sales and administrative office in Lafayette for our expanding Gulf of Mexico client base . " ( ( - - New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1610 . ) ) 
